<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-26-0462 </DOCNO><TEXT>The scope of duties to be fulfilled by analytical chemistry in nuclearengineering is described in detail by the example of the nuclear fuelcycle. The special problems encountered in the assay of radioactive samplematerial are dealt with extensively. The most currently used analyticalmethods are tabulated. The importance of automation is outlined.</TEXT></DOC>